reviews.headline: Not for your waterline
reviews.comments: If you want to use it for your waterline i would not recommend this. When i swatched it on my arm it was smooth.

reviews.headline: Awesome colorful eyeliner
reviews.comments: I own sooooo many purple eyeliners and this is the one I reach for the most. Especially the lilac/lavendar shade.  Its easy to apply, blend and really shows up even on fair skin.  The only con os tjay since it is so creamy it needs frequent sharpening and being dual ended it isnt a lot of product.  If you like impactful purple or blue eyeliner this is 10/10.  There are better products for the black & brown eyeliner category.  I want to try the cream/nude next!

reviews.headline: I love this gel pencil
reviews.comments:
I got the light blue Morphe pencil and was very pleased at the shimmer it has and how nicely it shows up
around my eyes. The other color is a very light blue, almost white, and it's great for enhancing areas around my eyes. The best part is that the color stays on and doesn't smudge.

reviews.headline: THE BEST!
reviews.comments: I have watery and sensitive eyes and i love these!! I have 3 different colors and i love them all. No eyeliner has stayed on my eyes that long without smudging flaking or causing irritation. The black is sooo dark its the blackest black ive ever used!!! Please always make these i have multiple back ups of each color i like.

reviews.headline: Okaaay, Morphe
reviews.comments: I had written this brand off due its shady dealings with even shadier influencers, but in the last month I've purchased an eyeshadow palette, an eye liner, their Cloudlight veils (like Hourglass), eyebrow pencil, creamy bronzer stick, lipgloss, and brush set. There is not a dud in the bunch. I especially love the pressed powder, bronzer, and brushes. I put this eyeliner on in store and walked around and around, and it stayed on! Excited to bring it on travel adventures.

reviews.headline: Long lasting no smudge perfect eyeliner
reviews.comments: I've tried every eyeliner made. This is the only one that actually lasts all day. No smudge, no flake, and I have supersentive eyes. I went months without eyeliner because of it. I love this 100%

reviews.headline: Don't use either side in the waterline
reviews.comments: I purchased the Friend/Foe combo. While the dark navy with sparkle side says to avoid use in waterline, the matte navy blue does not. However, when I used the matte side in my waterline, it was so scratchy and irritating that I had to take it off immediately. My eyes stayed irritated for the next three days. If you're going to try this, keep it on the upper lid only.

faceoff_positive.comments: To start off, i'd like to thank bzz agent for sending me this product to try out and give my honest review. now, I'd like to first say when i first saw the photo for this product, i initially thought the lighter color of the gel pencil would be a reddish color. when I received it in the mail, it definitely comes off more pink/magenta. This was a pleasant surprise for me, because when I tried it out on my waterline the payoff was amazing in contrast to my dark brown eyes. as for the darker color, I used this to make a small wing on my eyelid, and unfortunately the payoff wasn't as great as the lighter color, but you can definitely build it up with more layers to create a nice dark color. as for longevity, both colors definitely lasted a decent 8 hours without smudging. I have combination skin, with my cheek/nose area being more oily so my eye products tend to smudge onto my cheek area where it's oily. i did not have that with this product, which makes it great for nights looks and even day looks, as this pencil has its dark night color and light day color. all in all, I will definitely be using this pencil long term and will be recommending it to others. I just wish the darker color a bit more color payoff so I wouldn't have to build it up! But the lighter magenta color is beautiful, especially for those with darker eye colors like mine.
faceoff_positive.headline: A product with pretty good payoff

faceoff_negative.comments: I was excited to add some lip liner into my tinted lip balm routine, and these colors seemed perfect. When I received and opened, the stick colors didn't quite match the box and online pictures. The pink is lighter and the dark berry is a little more ashy than I wanted. They were still cute, so I paired each color with a few outfits and went about my day. The sticks came off really easily with drinking, eating, normal wear since they are creamy. Overall they are convenient and have a nice texture going on, but I would prefer something with longer lasting power and more true to advertised color.
faceoff_negative.headline: Goes on Smooth but Low Lasting Power
